        <opener>
          <dateline><l>A.+.M. College,</l><l>Raleigh, Feb. 28-'94</l></dateline>
          <salutation><l>Dear Sister,</l></salutation>
        </opener>
         <p><l>Your letter to me</l><l> was received Monday the 19<ord>th</ord></l><l>and I was glad to get it too, <del>as</del></l><l>it was the first time your</l><l>letters were more than a week </l><l>part. I dont believe any thing</l><l>unusual has happened since</l><l>I wrote to Lucy the first last</l><l>of the week. We did not have any</l><l>of that snow that you all</l><l>had, we had wind and a little</l><l>snow but did not any ^<ord>of the little</ord> stay on</l><l>the houses even.</l><l><add>...</add></l>
         <closer><l>I reckon Walter has written</l><l>you all the news so we</l><l>close with love to all I</l><l>shall ever remain your</l><l>loving Bro.</l></closer>
         <signed>G. J. Bullock</signed></p>
      </body>
